# Model and Contract Consistency

`ImageBlock` is the shared block contract:
- `x`, `y`, `width`, `height`: relative values in [0, 1]
- `offsetX`, `offsetY`: canvas pixel offsets
- `scale`: image zoom factor within block

Flutter-native `layoutConfig` contract is canonical:
- `canvasWidth`
- `canvasHeight`
- `isLongImage`
- `blocks[]` with `x/y/width/height/scale/offsetX/offsetY`

Rules:
- Do not rename/retype these fields in one side only.
- Any contract change must be updated on both Flutter and native sides in the same task.
- Document unit semantics when adding new fields (relative ratio vs canvas pixels vs render pixels).
- Prefer updating existing model fields over adding parallel contract models.
